grades.title: 7118LE
grades.summary: Density 918 kg/m3, MFR(2.16 kg)1 g/10 min
grades.description:
SUPEER™ Metallocene Linear Low Density Polyethylene (mLLDPE) 7118LE is a metallocene ethylene-hexene copolymer. It has a good processability and performs well in a wide range of general purpose and high performance blown film applications. Films produced with this grade offer good tensile and impact strength, puncture resistance and sealing properties. 
The resin contains anti-block and slip agent.
SABIC® mLLDPE 7118LE is typically used for applications like heavy duty bags, agriculture film, stretch hood, lamination film, frozen bags. 
Properties have been measured on blown film of 25 µm (mono layer) and BUR = 2.5
Typical processing conditions for SABIC® mLLDPE 7118LE: processing temperatures 180 - 230 °C.

This product is not intended for and must not be used in any pharmaceutical/medical applications.

grades.title: P8200RT
grades.description:
SUPEER™ Metallocene Linear Low Density Polyethylene (mLLDPE) P8200RT is an ethylene-octene copolymer produced via solution polymerization using metallocene
catalyst. SUPEER™ Metallocene Linear Low Density Polyethylene (mLLDPE) P8200RT performs well in a wide range of pipe applications with excellent long-term hydrostatic strength,
combined with good surface and superior processibility. It is designed to fulfill all the requirements of DIN 16833 / ISO 24033
for PE-RT Type II.
